In the `handleSearch` function at the bottom of the file, the focus index is set to the first visible match:

```js
const focusIndex =
  matchItems.findIndex((matchItem) =>
    visibleIds.has(matchItem.element.id),
  ) ?? null;

cb(matchItems, focusIndex);


```

So `onChange` does reset focus via `setFocusIndex(index)` where `index` comes from `handleSearch`. That seems fine.

But I'm noticing the `useEffect` that runs when the scene changes doesn't update the focus index—it only updates the search matches. The effect calls `handleSearch` with a callback that sets the matches but never calls `setFocusIndex` with the returned index.

